com.ibm.team.build.common.model
Interface IBuildSchedule

public interface IBuildSchedule

A build schedule. Schedule entries are either interval-based or time-based. Interval-based entries specify an interval in minutes, for example 20. This would schedule a build to run every 20 minutes. Time-based entries specify a specific hour and minute at which to start the build. If the entry has a valid interval (interval > 0), then the time-based values (hour and minute) are ignored.

Since:
0.5

void setBuildInterval(int minutes)
Deprecated. use IBuildScheduleEntry.setBuildInterval(int) and IBuildSchedule.setBuildScheduleEntries(List)

Set the build interval. The build will be scheduled every minutes minutes. The minimum valid value is 1 minute. Any value less than 1 means the build will not be scheduled on an interval. If a valid interval is provided, hour and minute are ignored.
